    "Other fields (Music applications)It has been established that GAN and its varieties, such as the C-RNN GAN proposed by Mogren et al. [94], the Object Reinforced GAN (ORGAN) discovered by Guimaraes et al.",
    "[95], and the SeqGAN presented by Yu et al. [96] may be useful in the area of music production.",
    "(Medical applications)The medical industry is one of the most significant applications for generative adversarial networks (GANs), where they are used for tasks such as the synthesis and design of DNA illustrated by Killoran et al. [97], chemGAN proposed by Behenda et al.",
    "[98], and medical imaging.",
    "Additionally, it is used in dental records [99] and suggestions [100] given by medical professionals."
